How will we handle looping?
LOOPS
TAILS
When encountering an opening [, if the current memory cell is nonzero, start executing the loop
When encountering a closing ], if the current memory cell is nonzero, we jump back to the matching [
A loop stack will store copies of the contents of currently executing loop(s), while a tail stack will store the code to be executed once the loop ends
Shortcut: Rust macros already have a perfectly good system for matching nested brackets -- let's use it!
